onto governorships in the gulf coast state of Veracruz and the
southeastern state of Oaxaca.
	   Official preliminary results were to be released later.
	   ``What we want for Aguascalientes is a transition that does not
hold back its progress, that does not cause a scandal,'' Felipe
Gonzalez Gonzalez of National Action told a news conference after
the nation's media declared him the winner.
	   According to Televisa's poll, Gonzalez Gonzalez captured 50
percent of the vote. The PRI's candidate, Hector Hugo Olivares
