<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Vietnam-War Bomb </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Three killed, two injured by war-era artillery shell
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ Three people were killed and two others
were seriously injured when a Vietnam War-era artillery shell
exploded in the central province of Ha Tinh, local police said
Monday.
	   The incident took place last Tuesday when the villagers tried to
set off the detonator so they could get to the explosives and sell
the shell for scrap iron, police said.
	   Casualties are reported virtually every week in southern and
central Vietnam, where many villagers risk their lives to collect
scrap iron from ordnance left over from the Vietnam War.
</TEXT>
