</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Macau-Piracy </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Macau police report largest seizure of pirated CDs
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HONG KONG (AP) _ Police in Macau have made their largest seizure
of pirated compact discs, discovering about 430,000 hidden in a
truck at the border between the Portuguese territory and the
Chinese mainland, news reports said Monday.
	   The Portuguese news agency LUSA, in a report from Macau, quoted
marine and customs police as estimating that the discs had a value
of about 5 million patacas (dlrs 645,000). It said they were found
in 400 boxes hidden under used iron plates.
	   They were seized on the border with the adjacent Zhuhai special
economic zone in China.
	   Macau and Hong Kong are regarded as important shipment and
production centers for pirated discs.
	   Macau, 40 miles (70 kilometers) west of Hong Kong, is due to
return to Chinese sovereignty on Dec. 20, 1999, after more than 400
years of Portuguese rule. 	   
</TEXT>
