<SLUG> BC-Mexico-Elections, 8th Ld,0164 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Partial results: Opposition wins Mexican gubernatorial vote
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: UPDATE with partial official results of 40 percent confirming
opposition headed for victory in Aguascalientes. Gonzalez Gonzalez
is cq in graf 2 &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos AGU101-103;OAX101-103 &QL; 
 &UR; By KEN GUGGENHEIM &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   AGUASCALIENTES, Mexico (AP) _ In a crucial victory ahead of the
2000 presidential elections, partial results showed the opposition
National Action Party on Sunday captured the governor's seat in the
central state of Aguascalientes.
	   With 40 percent of the vote counted early Monday, Felipe
Gonzalez Gonzalez of National Action was ahead with 53.12 percent
of the vote, the Aguascalientes State Electoral Council said.
	   The ruling Institutional Revolutionary Party's candidate, Hugo
Hector Hugo Olivares Ventura, trailed with 36.97. Alfonso Bernal
Sahagun of the center-left Democratic Revolution Party had 6
percent.
	    &UR; MORE
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Mexico-Elections, 8th Ld; CT:i; 
