<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Visiting Romanian Prime Minister Radu Vasile
said his country is willing to repatriate Jews whose property was
nationalized in Romania, Israel Radio reported Monday.
	   Vasile, who arrived Sunday for a four-day visit to Israel said
he would introduce legislation to the Romanian parliament on the
matter next month.
	   Vasile was scheduled to meet Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
Monday and with the representatives of the the Organization for the
Restitution of Jewish property on Tuesday.
