<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Tajikistan-Smugglers Killed </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Two suspected smugglers killed on Tajik-Afghan border
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russian troops guarding Tajikistan's southern
border killed two suspected drug smugglers and captured four more
men in a shootout, officials said Monday.
	   The gun battle took place Sunday night on the frontier with
Afghanistan, the site of frequent clashes between Russian troops
and drug smugglers, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported.
	   The Russian troops also seized 30 kilograms (66 pounds) of opium
from the men, the report added.
	   The Russian border guards have seized more than 700 kilograms
(1,500 pounds) of drugs this year, the report added.
	   The 25,000 Russian troops in Tajikistan supported the government
during a five-year civil war that formally ended last year. The
troops have remained to guard against smugglers bringing drugs and
weapons from Afghanistan.
	   (gm) 	   
