<HEADLINE>
Russian prosecutor dies after driving car into canal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The attorney general for the St. Petersburg region
died after he drove his Mercedes sedan off a bridge and plunged
into one of the city's canals, news reports said Monday.
	   Georgy Porukov was alone in his car Sunday evening when he
crashed into the canal in St. Petersburg, Russian news agencies
reported.
	   Porukov, 59, had worked at the regional prosecutor's office
since 1984.
