<SLUG> BC-Israel-Romania, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Romanian premier: Romania willing to return property to Jews
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: CORRECTS that Vasile said Romania will make reparations,
UPDATES with quote, upgrades attribution &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   JERUSALEM (AP) _ Visiting Romanian Prime Minister Radu Vasile
said Monday that he will submit legislation in parliament next
month to return property to Jews whose property was nationalized
after World War II.
	   ``The bill presents a global solution for Romania to return
property to all former owners, not only Jews,'' said Vasile, who
arrived Sunday for a four-day visit to Israel.
	   Vasile was scheduled to meet Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
later Monday, and with the representatives of the World Jewish
Restitution Organization on Tuesday.
	   Some 400,000 Jews _ half the Romanian Jewish population _
perished in World War II, when Romania was allied with Nazi
Germany. Many others left the country in the years after the war,
when hundreds of Jewish properties were nationalized.
	   Foreign Minister Andrei Plesu said there were now only 12,000
Jews in Romania, but that Romanian Jews living outside the country
were expected to ask for the return of their property as well.
	   Romania's president, Emil Constantinescu, won praise from
Romanian Jewish leaders last year for publicly acknowledging the
country's complicity in the persecution and murder of Jews in the
Holocaust.
	   dk-hla
</TEXT>
