<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Ukraine-Chernobyl </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chernobyl's only working reactor shut down
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KIEV, Ukraine (AP) _ The only working reactor at the Chernobyl
nuclear power plant shut down automatically because of an electric
transformer malfunction, officials said Monday.
	   No radiation leaks have occurred since the shutdown on Sunday
afternoon, said the state company Energoatom, which runs Ukraine's
nuclear plants. The reactor will undergo repairs until Friday,
Energoatom said.
	   The accident, albeit minor, underscored recent warnings by
Ukraine's top nuclear safety official, who recently noted the
growing number of malfunctions at the country's five atomic power
plants.
	   Oleksandr Smyshlyayev, who heads the Environment Protection
Ministry's nuclear division, blamed outdated equipment and the
failure to observe safety rules for the mounting breakdowns.
	   The Chernobyl plant originally had four working nuclear
reactors.
	   However, reactor No. 4 was destroyed in a 1986 explosion, the
world's worst nuclear accident. Another reactor was shut down after
being badly damaged by a 1991 fire, and a third is not operational.
	   Ukraine relies on nuclear plants to produce more than half of
its electricity, and says it does not have enough money to convert
to other forms of energy or make wide-ranging safety improvements.
	   (sms/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
