<HEADLINE>
Uzbekistan cuts gas supplies to Kyrgyzstan, citing overdue
</HEADLINE>
payments &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Uzbekistan has cut gas supplies to its Central
Asian neighbor, Kyrgyzstan, citing an overdue bill of dlrs 2.5
million, a news report said Monday.
	   The cutoff was affecting Kyrgyzstan's capital, Dushanbe, and
other northern regions of the country, the Interfax news agency
reported.
	   The government in Kyrgyzstan, a small, mountainous agricultural
nation, held an emergency meeting Monday to try to solve the
problem, the report said.
	   Kyrgyzstan has been unable to make payments because it needed
extra money to cope with a series of floods in the south of the
country during the spring, officials told Interfax.
	   (gm) 	   
