<HEADLINE>
Protesters threaten to block Russian-U.S. military maneuvers
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ About 200 demonstrators in Russia's eastern port
city of Vladivostok staged a protest Monday and said they would try
to disrupt military maneuvers this week involving Russian forces
and the U.S. Marines, news reports said.
	   The protesters called on anybody with a boat to block the August
6 and 7 maneuvers, which involve training for a response to a
natural disasters, the Interfax news agency said.
	   Among other exercises, U.S. Marines are to conduct mock landings
