<SLUG> BC-Russia-Killing </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Chief of Russian gas company killed
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Attackers shot and killed the president of a gas
company early Monday morning in Moscow, a news report said.
	   Yuri Bezruchenko, head of Promstroigaz, was found dead inside
his Mercedes with two bullet wounds to the head, the ITAR-Tass news
agency reported.
	   Police were trying to determine whether the shooting was related
to Bezruchenko's business activities, the report said.
	   Many of Russia's contract killings involve business rivals
seeking to settle scores. Few of the cases are ever solved.
