<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, UPDATE </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Ammunition seized in northern Albania
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TIRANA, Albania (AP) _ Police have seized about 150,000 rounds
of sm,all arms ammunition in the northern town of Bajram Curri in
an area used by Kosovo Albanian rebels as a sanctuary, the Interior
Ministry said Monday.
	   Ministry spokesman Artan Bizhga said that two people were
arrested after the police stopped their truck carrying the
ammunition Sunday. The two were not identified.
	   Serbian authorities have often accused the Albanian government
of complicity in weapons smuggling to KLA fighters in Kosovo.
	   Albania has denied the allegations. Last week, Albanian Prime
Minister Fatos Nano ordered the government to prepare a plan to
halt ``unlawful and criminal activity'' in the northeast of the
country.
