<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Egypt-Wedding Death,0159 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Singer shot in celebratory gunfire at wedding
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CAIRO, Egypt (AP) _ A singer performing at a wedding was
accidentally shot and killed by the groom's brother, who was firing
an automatic rifle in celebration of the marriage, police said
Monday.
	   The victim was identified as Ayman Abdel-Wahab, 22.
	   Police said he died Saturday after he was shot by Gamal
Abdel-Gawad, who was firing in the air to celebrate the wedding of
his brother in the village of Mir in southern Egypt. Abdel-Gawad
was taken into custody, police said.
	   Despite a government ban, firing guns is a still common way to
celebrate weddings in southern Egypt.
	   The singer was the third person to died in celebratory gunfire
in recent days. Last week, a bride and groom were shot dead at
their wedding when a guest misjudged his aim while trying to fire
over their heads. The bride's mother is recovering in a hospital
from a gunshot wound. 	   
