<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-Aircraft </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Malaysia's first homemade airplane takes off
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ The first made-in-Malaysia
aircraft took off from a Kuala Lumpur airport Monday, the national
news agency Bernama reported.
	   The two-seat sports plane would be sold at about 80,000 ringgit
(dlrs 20,000), Transport Minister Ling Liong Sik said after he
inaugurated the airplane.
	   Work on Langkawi 1, designed from blueprints purchased from
Zenith Air of Canada, started in 1996. It was a cooperative effort
of private and public companies.
	   It was not known when the plane would be on the market.
	   ``The aircraft, which is attractively priced, will make flying
affordable to Malaysians,'' Ling said. ``This will eventually help
to introduce and popularize the flying culture in Malaysia and
neighboring countries.''	   
