<SLUG> BC-Hong Kong-Layoffs </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fashion chain closes 23 outlets in Hong Kong
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; With BC-Hong Kong-Economy &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   HONG KONG (AP) _ Fashion retailer Theme International Holdings
Ltd. announced Monday that it was closing 23 outlets in Hong Kong
and laying off 86 employees because of the economic downturn.
	   The Hong Kong company said the outlets belonged to its wholly
owned subsidiary, The Shop Clothing Ltd.
	   ``In view of the severe retail downturn in Hong Kong, the
directors regrettably decided that the closure of the shops was the
only sensible option we could take to enable us to return the group
to profitability,'' chairman and chief executive Kenneth Lai
Hin-fung said.
	   The company earlier had to seek an 80 million Hong Kong dollar
(U.S. dlrs 10.2 million) loan from its major shareholder, China
Everbright Ltd., and is currently restructuring its operations.
	   Theme said its flagship stores in two major shopping malls and
10 other shops in Hong Kong and Macau are operating normally, as
are its shops and department store concessions in China and Taiwan.	   
</TEXT>
