<SLUG> BC-EU-Greece </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EU clears dlrs 68 million for Greece
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) - The European Union has cleared 62
million European currency units (dlrs 68 million) for projects in
Greece aimed at improving roads and the environment, it said
Monday.
	   In a statement, the EU executive Commission said dlrs 30 million
will help finance a road-building project. A further dlrs 38
million will go to several environmental programs, it said.
	   The funds are part of the EU's so-called cohesion funds for
those countries in the 15-nation bloc that have weaker economies
than the others.
	   For the 1993-1999 period the recipients are Ireland, Spain,
Portugal and Greece.
