<HEADLINE>
Gunmen rob maternity hospital
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ Three gunmen robbed an Athens maternity
hospital Monday, slightly injuring a doctor who attempted to stop
them, local media said.
	   The gunmen entered the accounting office of Iaso hospital, one
of the capital's largest private maternity facilities, fired three
shots into the ceiling and took 100,000 drachmas (dlrs 339).
	   They then stole 10 million drachmas (dlrs 33,900) from a
National Bank of Greece branch located inside the hospital and next
door to the accounting office. They fled the hospital in a car.
	   A doctor, Antonis Mitsis, was slightly injured when one of the
robbers hit him on the head with a gun as he tried to stop them
from leaving the hospital.
	   The hospital is located next door to the Athens Olympic Sports
Complex, where the World Basketball Championships are being held.
	   (eb) 	   
