<HEADLINE>
Jonk joins Sheffield Wednesday
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SHEFFIELD, England (AP) _ Dutch World Cup midfielder Wim Jonk
will join Premier League soccer team Sheffield Wednesday in a 2.5
million-pound (dlrs 4.1 million) transfer from PSV Eindhoven, the
English club said Monday.
	   Sheffield Wednesday secretary Graham Mackrell confirmed Monday
that Jonk had signed a three-year contract and would arrive at
Hillsborough on Tuesday.
	   Jonk was a key member of the Netherlands' World Cup squad _
semifinalists at France 98 _ and had been linked with moves to
Tottenham and Nottingham Forest before signing with the Owls.
	   The 31-year-old Dutch international is Danny Wilson's first
major signing since he became manager at Hillsborough last month.
	   Mackrell said Wilson would be given more funding to recruit more
top line players before the start of the season.
	   ``Naturally, we're delighted to have landed Wim,'' he said.
	   Jonk signed after a delegation from Sheffield Wednesday flew to
the Netherlands to finalize a deal with PSV Eindhoven.
	   (jp)
