<HEADLINE>
Kosovo Albanians caught at Hungarian-Serb border
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) _ Forty-five Kosovo Albanians were
detained after entering Hungary illegally Monday in an attempt to
get to Austria and Germany, the state news agency MTI reported.
	   The group of 19 women, 15 men and 11 children was caught between
Morahalom and Asotthalom, two small settlements 160 kilometers (100
miles) southeast of Budapest.
	   They claimed they had paid 300 to 2,000 German marks (dlrs
150-1,000) to unidentified helpers to get to the West.
	   The illegal aliens were taken into border guards' custody.
Authorities have yet to decide their fate.
	   If they are determined to be war refugees, they will be given
haven at least for the duration of the conflict.
