<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-Shipping </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Malaysian shipping line launches service to Chittagong, Bangladesh
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ Malaysia International Shipping
Corp. Berhad said Monday it will launch service to Chittagong,
Bangladesh, this week.
	   MISC, Malaysia's leading international shipping line will send
its first freighter, the Bunga Mas Enam, from Port Klang on
Saturday. The ship is due in Chittagong Aug. 13 and back in Port
Klang Aug. 24, the company said in a statement.
	   The service is jointly operated with Xpress Feeders Group Ltd.,
with both providing one compatible geared vessel each.
	   Apart from promoting direct trade between Malaysia and
Bangladesh, the Chittagong-Port Klang service will encourage main
line operators to use Port Klang to transship cargo bound for
Bangladesh due to the low handling cost at Port Klang, the
statement said.	   
</TEXT>
