<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Spain-Immigrants </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Spanish police detain 83 would-be immigrants
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ALGECIRAS, Spain (AP) _ Police detained 83 would-be immigrants
Monday including 57 they believed were trying to enter Spain
clandestinely after crossing the often treacherous Strait of
Gibraltar by night in rudimentary single-engine boats.
	   Police said they found between five and 10 kilograms of hashish
in one of the boats which was carrying 30 men. The 30 were brought
before court while police investigated who was responsoible for
smuggling the drug.
	   Twenty five men and two women traveled in the other boat. Both
vessels were spotted just off the coast from Carnero Point on
Spain's southern tip before 2 a.m. (0000 gmt), the police spokesman
said. He added that all 57 were Moroccan.
	   In a separate incident, police detained 22 Algerians and four
Moroccans found hidden in an Italian truck traveling towards the
French border early Monday.
	   Fleeing poverty at home, thousands of people attempt each year
to cross the Mediterranean Sea from North Africa and enter unseen
into Europe. Almost all the would-be immigrants are men and most
are from Morocco.
	   Some 20 would-be immigrants are believed to have drowned when
their boat overturned close to the Spanish coast last week.
	   Those caught in Spain or trying to make the crossing are
repatriated.
	   (cg)
</TEXT>
