 &UR; RECASTS first three grafs &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   WOLVERHAMPTON, England (AP) _ A judge on Monday jailed the
brother of British Olympic javelin gold medallist Tessa Sanderson
for 18 months for killing a man outside a nightclub.
	   Eric Sanderson, who was working as a bouncer, punched Martin
Leaver, 36, in the face, causing him to fall and hit his head on a
sidewalk. Leaver sustained serious brain damage and died later in
hospital.
	   Sanderson, 35, gave himself up to police the day after the April
attack and later pleaded guilty to manslaughter.
