<HEADLINE>
Vatican says it seeking solution for occupation
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   VATICAN CITY (AP) _ Vatican diplomats are pressing French
authorities to review the cases of immigrants seeking residence
permits who have occupied the Vatican's embassy in Paris for three
days.
	   In its first official comment Monday, the Vatican said 12 people
forced their way into the embassy Saturday.
	   The 12 were among a group of some 300 Africans who occupied the
Saint Bernard church in Paris for two months in 1996. The Africans
were without residence permits.
	   Police stormed the church and expelled the group, but many have
since become legal residents of France.
	   The Saint Bernard group now serves as a model for other illegal
immigrants seeking papers to remain in France.
	   The Vatican said its embassy was asking French authorities ``to
review the cases'' of the occupiers.
	   (vls)
