	   AP-Europe Advisory
	   Editors: The following stories have moved or will move on the
European circuits of the Associated Press by 1600GMT, unless
otherwise noted.
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ Government forces overran another ethnic
Albanian stronghold in Kosovo despite Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic's pledge that the offensive was over. Relief agencies
said tens of thousands of civilians had been displaced by fighting
which flared over the weekend. YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO.
	   VIENNA _ Hopes are fading for 10 men buried last month in an
Austrian mine after cameras and microphones lowered into an
emergency shaft failed to detect signs of life in the chamber where
the men were believed to be trapped. AUSTRIA-MINE RESCUE.
	   FRANKFURT _ Warning against ``economic recklessness,'' Germany's
atomic energy industry Monday attacked plans by the Social
Democrats to start closing nuclear power plants if they succeed in
unseating Chancellor Helmut Kohl. GERMANY-NUCLEAR.
