<SLUG> BC-Germany-Politics </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Kohl's party says rebuilding east Germany will retain priority
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SCHWERIN, Germany (AP) _ Rebuilding Germany's former communist
east will continue to have priority if Chancellor Helmut Kohl is
re-elected to a fifth term, his parliamentary leader said Monday.
	   Although unemployment in the struggling east remains twice that
of western Germany, Wolfgang Schaeuble said east Germany's economy
was stabilizing.
	   He credited the greater flexibility and innovation of business,
labor and government in the east, and said Kohl's government wanted
to spread those advantages to all of Germany to fight unemployment,
currently at 10.5 percent nationwide.
	   Schaeuble was in northeastern Schwerin presenting the second
part of a three-part campaign platform for Kohl's Christian
Democrats and their Bavarian sister party, the Christian Social
Union.
