<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, UPDATE </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Rugova group criticizes leadership of Kosovo Liberation Army
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia (AP) -- The information outlet controlled
by Albanian political leader Ibrahim Rugova for the first time
criticized the leadership of the Kosovo Liberation Army in what
appeared to be a bid to marginalize extremists in the group.
	   A statement by the Kosovo Information Center said Albanians
``who respect institutions'' headed by Rugova ``are revolted by the
careerism of those who have shabbily headed the KLA.''
	   The United States and European powers are urging the KLA to
approve formation of a committee under Rugova to enter talks with
Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic on the future of the majority
Albanian province.
	   KLA officials are expected to give their answer this week.
	   The statement carefully avoided criticizing the KLA as a whole
and instead was directed against radicals who reject Rugova because
of his non-violent stand.
	   The divisions come as Serb forces have dealt a severe setback to
the KLA, overruning several key villages and splitting
KLA-controlled territory.
	   rr/ih/ds
</TEXT>
