<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Vietnam-Crime </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Vietnam sets up national program to combat crimes
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HANOI, Vietnam (AP) _ Prime Minister Phan Van Khai has approved
a national program aimed at lowering Vietnam's growing crime rate,
local press reported Monday.
	   A circular, signed by Khai on Friday, said efforts will be
concentrated on fighting corruption, organized criminal gangs, drug
trafficking and addiction, and trade in women and children. The
national program will be headed by a deputy prime minister.
	   Crime has been rising since the communist country launched an
economic reform program in the mid-1980s.	   
</TEXT>
