<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sudan-Truce </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Sudan declared unilateral truce in southern Sudan
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; URGENT &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) _ Sudan announced Monday a unilateral
cease-fire throughout southern Sudan, where war has caused a
worsening famine. The government urged rebels to follow suit.
	   ``The announcement comes as a further measure in the continuing
effort by the government to contain the humanitarian situation in
southern Sudan,'' a government statement said.
	   The declaration expands the scope of a limited three-month
cease-fire reached between the government and the rebel Sudan
People's Liberation Army in July. It comes on the eve of peace
talks between the warring parties in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.
	    &UR; MORE
 &UR; mo-tt-as
</TEXT>
