<SLUG> BC-Netherlands-Gay Games Firing,0208 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Managing director of Gay Games dismissed for overspending
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) _ The managing director of the 1998
Gay Games was fired for overspending just after the Olympics-style
event began.
	   The board of directors for the quadrennial homosexual sports and
cultural festival issued a statement Monday, saying it had
``revoked the mandate'' of Dutchman Marc Janssens on Sunday, the
day after the opening ceremonies.
	   ``The reason is that Mr. Janssens made commitments outside the
approved budget, commitments that were also bigger than his
authority,'' the statement said. It did not elaborate.
	   ``We have no overview of the complete situation,'' said Games
spokesman Paul van Yperen, adding the directors are still
investigating the extent of the financial problem.
	   The Gay Games, which began on Saturday and run through Aug. 8,
are expected to attract 15,000 participants and 200,000 visitors
from 66 countries.
	   The event is costing 14 million guilders (dlrs 7 million).
Organizers received 3 million guilders (dlrs 1.5 million) in
government subsidies and another 3 millions guilders (dlrs 1.5
million) from corporate sponsors such as KLM Royal Dutch Airlines
and Kodak. 	   
</TEXT>
