responsibility'' for assuring that international aid organizations
could deliver relief supplies to the refugees and that diplomatic
observers could escort them back to their homes.
	   Speaking to reporters in Pristina, Hill said he was waiting for
signs those promises would be fulfilled.
	   ``I'm not interested in anyone's assurances,'' he said. ``We
don't have facts on the grounds as far as I can see.''
	   Another UNHCR official, Mons Nyberg, said access had been ``on
and off,'' with police sometimes holding his teams at checkpoints
for hours before allowing them to proceed.
