<HEADLINE>
Boy group hits the road one more time before disbanding
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ Caught in the Act, one of Europe's
most successful boy groups, will make a quick farewell tour this
month before disbanding after six years together, a spokeswoman
said Monday.
	   The two Dutch members, Eloy de Jong and Batsiann Ragas, and
Benjamin Boyce and Lee Baxter of Britain, all now in their mid-20s,
will hit the road Saturday and play their final show in Magdeburg,
in eastern Germany on Aug. 16, said the spokeswoman for ZYX Records
in Frankfurt.
	   The four singers, whose hits include ``You Know,'' ``Do It for
Love,'' and ``Baby Come Back,'' also plan a greatest hits album in
September.
