<HEADLINE>
Sailor attacks captain and crew member, then sets himself ablaze
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ A sailor aboard a luxury yacht Monday used
a hatchet to injure his captain and another crew member, before
dousing himself with gasoline and setting his body ablaze.
	   According to the Merchant Marine Ministry, four Greek and seven
Canadian passengers aboard the yacht Thelginos used fire
extinguishers to put out Robert Giannousis. The passengers were not
identified. The yacht had three crew members.
	   Giannousis seriously injured Capt. Nicolas Klaromenos, 56, and
sailor Vasilis Hasandras, 45, before setting himself ablaze.
	   The ministry said Giannousis was listed in serious condition at
a health center on the Aegean Sea island of Alonissos. The captain
and sailor were also hospitalized.
	   The ministry said it had no further information on the incident,
which occurred while the yacht was anchored off a bay in Alonissos.
	   An investigation was underway to determine the reasons which led
Giannousis to go on a rampage in the early morning hours, the
ministry said.
