<HEADLINE>
Dutch striker remaining with AC Milan
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MILAN, Italy (AP) _ Dutch striker Patrick Kluivert has turned
down an offer from Manchester United to remain with AC Milan, the
Italian soccer club reported Monday.
	   The 22-year-old forward reached his decision during a meeting in
Amsterdam with his agent and Milan's director-general, Ariedo
Bradia.
	   Manchester United chairman Martin Edwards said Thursday that
Milan had accepted an offer, worth a reported 9 million pounds
(dlrs 14.8 million), for the the Dutchman, who starred for his
country during the World Cup in France.
	   Kluivert's contract with Milan, linking him to the club through
June 30, 2001, remains unchanged, the team said.
	   He reportedly received a small increase in his compensation.
