<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Yugoslavia-Kosovo, UPDATE </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Serb sources: one hundred-eighteen still missing in Kosovo
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) _ Albanian guerrillas in Kosovo have
kidnapped 171 people, mostly Serbs, since fighting escalated
earlier this year in the restive Serbian province. Most of them are
still missing or presumed dead, Serb sources said Monday,
	   The total of 171 included 125 Serbs, 37 ethnic Albanians who
were loyal to the authorities, six Gypsies, one ethnic Bulgarian,
one Muslim and one citizen of neighboring Macedonia.
	   Thirty-one have been released by the Kosovo Liberation Army,
upon insistence from international humanitarian organizations and
seven managed to escape, which left 133 still missing.
	   The summary released by Media Center, based in Kosovo capital
Pristina and close to the authorities, said 25 are presumed dead -
15 civilians and 10 policemen - but fears increase with time about
all others who may have long been dead.
	   An Albanian source, gathering information mostly on the other
side of the conflict, among Kosovo's idependence-seeking ethnic
Albanians, has said that a total of 400 people, mostly Kosovo
Albanians, have gone missing since the fighting escalated in
February.
	   (ds/ms)
</TEXT>
