<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Skies will be partly cloudy across the region overnight.
Scattered showers are possible, mainly over the U.S. Virgin
Islands, along the north and east coasts of Puerto Rico and across
the coastal waters.
	   Low temperatures will range from the mid 60s over the higher
spots of interior Puerto Rico, between 75 and 80 degrees elsewhere.
The winds will be variable at less than 10 mph.
	   High pressure at the low to middle levels of the atmosphere will
continue to produce generally fair and dry weather across Puerto
Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands through Monday.
	   However, an upper-level disturbance will combine with daytime
heating, the sea breeze and orographic effects to produce scattered
showers and isolated thunderstorms across the western interior and
western sections of Puerto Rico Monday afternoon.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly sunny in the morning. Partly cloudy in the
afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers. Possible
thunderstorms inland. High around 90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A 30 percent chance of mainly coastal
showers. Low 75 to 80. Wind light from the east.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 40 chance of showers. Isolated
afternoon thunderstorms. High near 90. Wind east at 15 to 20 mph.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly cloudy morning with a 20 percent chance of
showers. Mostly sunny in the afternoon. High 85 to 90. Wind east at
10 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 75 to 80. Wind east at 5 to 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Variably cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers,
mainly in the morning. Isolated thunderstorms. High 85 to 90. Wind
east 15 to 20 mph.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly sunny in the morning. Partly cloudy in the
afternoon with a 30 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms,
mostly inland and west. High 90 to 95. Wind east 10 to 15 mph
except southeast along the coast.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy in the evening with a 20 percent chance
of showers, mostly in the east. Low 70 to near 80. Wind light from
the east.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers and
thunderstorms, mainly in east during the morning and in the west
during the afternoon. High around 90. Wind east 15 to 20 mph,
except southeast along the coast.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Sunny in the morning. Partly cloudy in the afternoon
with a 40 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms. High 85 to
90. Wind east 10 to 15 mph except variable less than 10 mph along
the coast in the afternoon.
	   Tonight... A 20 percent chance of showers in the evening on the
coast, then becoming generally fair. Low 65 to 75. Wind east at 5
to 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly sunny in the morning. Mostly cloudy in the
afternoon with a 50 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms,
some with heavy rain. High 85 to 90. Wind east 15 to 20 mph, except
variable less than 10 mph along the coast in the afternoon.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Sunny in the morning. Mostly cloudy in the afternoon
with a 50 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms. High from 75
to 80 in the mountains, 85 to 95 in lower elevations. Wind east 10
to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Decreasing cloudiness and showers before midnight,
then becoming generally fair. 30 percent chance of showers, mainly
in the evening. Low 65 to 70 in the mountains, 70 to near 80 in
lower valleys. Wind east at 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Mostly sunny in the morning. Increasing clouds in the
afternoon with a 70 percent chance of showers and thunderstorms,
some with heavy rain. High from 75 to 80 in the mountains, 80 to 90
in lower elevations. Wind east 15 to 20 mph.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers. High
90 to 95. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Tonight... Partly cloudy. A 40 percent chance of showers. Low
around 80. Wind east 10 mph.
	   Tuesday... Partly cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers or
thunderstorms. High around 90. Wind east 15 to 20 mph.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   This afternoon... Wind variable, mainly east 5 to 10 kt. Near
shore seas 3 ft or less; offshore seas 3 to 4 ft. Widely scattered
showers. Wind and seas higher near isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind becoming east to southeast at 10 to 15 kt. Seas
2 to 4 ft. Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind east, increasing to 15 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 5 ft.
Widely scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   This afternoon... Wind variable, mainly east around 10 kt. Seas
2 to 3 ft, except seas to 4 ft anegada passage. Widely scattered
showers. Wind and seas higher near isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind becoming east to southeast 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2
to 4 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind east, increasing to 15 to 20 kt. Seas 3 to 4 ft,
except seas building 5 to 6 ft in the Anegada Passage and southeast
waters. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   This afternoon... Wind variable 5 to 10 kt. Seas 2 ft or less.
Widely scattered showers. Wind and seas higher and visibility below
1 nm near isolated afternoon thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind east 5 to 10 kt. Seas 2 ft or less. Widely
scattered showers. Isolated evening thunderstorms.
	   Tuesday... Wind variable, mainly east 10 to 15 kt. Seas 3 ft or
less. Widely scattered showers. Isolated afternoon thunderstorms.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Tuesday night through Friday... The next tropical wave will move
into the local area Tuesday night and Wednesday. Otherwise, weak
high pressure will prevail across the northeast Caribbean through
Friday. Wind 20 kt or less. Seas 6 ft or less.
</TEXT>
