w2875 &Cx1f; wstm-
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Turkey-Chechnya 1stLd   08-03 0147
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Turkey-Chechnya, 1st Ld </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Turkey keeps Chechen president at a distance during visit
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: LEADS to CORRECT weary to wary in 4th graf Turkey is etc &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos planned &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ISTANBUL, Turkey (AP) _ Turkey kept Chechen President Aslan
Maskhadov at a distance Monday, insisting that his four-day visit
was a private one that did not include official meetings with
Turkish leaders.
	   Maskhadov, who has been seeking support for Chechnya's
recognition as an independent state, arrived in Istanbul Sunday.
	   Although many here sympathize with largely Muslim Chechnya's
demands for independence, Turkey, which is fighting
autonomy-seeking Kurdish insurgents itself, does not recognize
Chechnya's independence.
	   Turkey is also said to be wary of damaging its ties with Moscow,
which insists that Chechnya is part of Russia.
	   Chechnya claimed, 5th graf
	   (fd)
</TEXT>
