<SLUG> BC-Spain-Immigrants,0204 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Spanish police detain 83 would-be immigrants
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ALGECIRAS, Spain (AP) _ Police detained Monday 57 Moroccans they
believed were trying to sneak into Spain after crossing the often
treacherous Strait of Gibraltar by night in two single-engine
boats, one of which also carried a cargo of hashish.
	   Police said they found between five and 10 kilograms (11 and 22
pounds) of hashish in a boat that was also carrying 30 men. All 30
were detained while police investigated who was responsible for
smuggling the drugs.
	   The other boat carried 25 men and two women. Both vessels were
spotted just off the coast from Carnero Point on Spain's southern
tip before 2 a.m., the police spokesman said.
	   In a separate incident, police detained 22 Algerians and four
Moroccans found hidden in an Italian truck traveling towards the
French border early Monday.
	   Fleeing poverty at home, thousands of people attempt each year
to cross the Mediterranean Sea from North Africa and sneak into
Europe. Almost all are men and most are from Morocco.
	   Those caught are repatriated.
	   Some 20 would-be immigrants are believed to have drowned when
their boat overturned close to the Spanish coast last week. 	   
</TEXT>
