<HEADLINE>
Mixed day for Swedes as Johansson exits, Gustafsson advances
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) _ Sweden's Thomas Johansson was the
first seeded casualty Monday in the Grolsch Open ATP clay court
tennis tourney, upset 0-6, 6-4, 7-6 (7-5) by Italian Galo Blanco.
	   Johansson, seeded No.4 here and 34 on the ATP tour rankings,
frittered away a 4-2 second-set lead against the 104th-ranked
Italian in the first match of main draw.
	   But the next match up on centre court saw Swedish third seed
Magnus Gustafsson make short work of Brazilian Fernando Meligeni
6-4, 6-3.
	   Two more seeds booked last-16 berths at the Bosbaan tennis
complex with straight sets wins on a first day free of the rain
which has dogged Dutch tennis this summer.
	   Australian No. 6 Richard Fromberg ousted Andrei Pavel of Romania
6-3, 6-4 and Slovakian No. 7 Dominik Hrbaty downed Belgium Filip
Dewulf, 6-3, 7-5.
	   The longest match of the day was between two unseeded players.
Italian Davide Sanguinetti came back from a first set tiebreaker
loss to eliminate Spaniard Alex Calatrava 6-7 (7-3), 6-2, 7-5.
	   Top-seeded Slovakian Karol Kucera starts his campaign in this
dlrs 500,000 tournament Tuesday, with a first-round matchup against
Russian Marat Safin.
	   (sc)	   
