<SLUG> BC-Greece-Yacht,0166 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Sailor attacks captain and crew member, then sets himself ablaze
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ A sailor aboard a luxury yacht attacked
his captain and another crew member with a hatchet Monday and then
doused himself with gasoline and set himself ablaze.
	   According to the Merchant Marine Ministry, four Greek and seven
Canadian passengers aboard the yacht Thelginos used fire
extinguishers to put out Robert Giannousis. The yacht had three
crew members.
	   Capt. Nicolas Klaromenos, 56, and sailor Vasilis Hasandras, 45,
were seriously injured in the attack.
	   Giannousis was listed in serious condition at a health center on
the Aegean Sea island of Alonissos, the ministry said. The captain
and sailor were also hospitalized.
	   The ministry said it had no further information on the incident,
which occurred while the yacht was anchored off a bay in Alonissos.
	   An investigation was underway to determine why Giannousis went
on a rampage, the ministry said. 	   
