<SLUG> BC-Rwanda-Congo-Rebellion, 4th Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Eastern Kivu region in open rebellion against Kabila
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: AMs. UPDATES in grafs 3-5 with comments from Congolese
military commander in Bukavu; raises background on Banyamulenge
rebellion; Edits slightly; no pickup &QL; 
 &UR; By HRVOJE HRANJSKI &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   KIGALI, Rwanda (AP) _ The Kivu region of eastern Congo is in
open rebellion against the government of President Laurent Kabila,
a Rwandan official said Monday.
	   The official, who spoke on condition that he not be further
identified, said the 700-kilometer (435-mile) stretch between
Kalemie and Beni in South and North Kivu provinces was up in arms.
	   Contacted by telephone in Bukavu, the capital of South Kivu
province, Maj. Ilunga Kabambi, the commander of the Congolese army
in the South Kivu region, said he and members of the 222nd Brigade
were ``not in agreement with the president.''
	   He said the city at the south end of Lake Kivu was calm after
``some trouble'' and confirmed reports that several dozen
Banyamulenge or ethnic Tutsi officers and soldiers, who had b	   
</TEXT>
