<SLUG> BC-Russia-Blast </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Teen dies from burns, raising death toll in Moscow blast to seven
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ A severely burned 17-year-old girl died Monday
from her wounds, bringing the death toll in an apartment gas
explosion to seven, a news agency reported.
	   A column of apartments in a 10-story building in eastern Moscow
was demolished from top to bottom by the explosion on July 29.
	   Rescuers pulled nine people from the rubble, but only three were
alive. The dead included a child and a couple engaged to be
married, officials and neighbors said.
	   The latest victim had been burned over 90 percent of her body,
and doctors had given her little chance of survival, the ITAR-Tass
news agency reported.
	   Officials have said the explosion was caused by negligence by a
tenant in the third-floor apartment, who died in the blast.
	   (mr) 	   
