w1092 &Cx1f; wstm-
r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-StVincent-Calypsonian     08-03 0098
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-St Vincent-Calypsonian,0097 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Calypso singer Lord Hawke found dead
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KINGSTOWN, St. Vincent (AP) _ Calypso singer Lloyd Providence,
better known as Lord Hawke, was found dead Monday morning in his
home on the Caribbean island of St. Vincent, police reported.
	   Providence, 54, appeared to have died from natural causes, they
said. Investigators were performing an autopsy.
	   Providence was widely considered a master of Caribbean calypso,
a heavily rhythmic music with African roots and lyrics rich in
political satire. He performed throughout the Caribbean and in New
York. 	   
