<HEADLINE>
Giants beat Phillies 6-1; Expos beat Padres 6-1
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PHILADELPHIA (AP) _ Danny Darwin won for the first time in nine
starts since July 8 and Barry Bonds drove in two runs Monday as the
San Francisco Giants beat the Philadelphia Phillies 6-1 to complete
a four-game sweep.
	   Darwin (7-9), who had lost six consecutive decisions, allowed
four hits in five shutout innings, striking out three and walking
three.
	   Carlton Loewer (5-4) allowed three runs and seven hits in six
innings, struck out seven and walked one.
 &UR; Expos 6, Padres 1
	   MONTREAL (AP) _ Dustin Hermanson took a shutout into the ninth
and Vladimir Guerrero hit a two-run, first-inning homer.
	   Hermanson (9-9) matched his season high with eight strikeouts
and walked four, allowing four hits in 8 2-3 innings. With two outs
in the ninth, Greg Myers hit an RBI single, and Steve Kline came in
for the final out.
	   Brian Boehringer (5-2), making his first start of the season,
allowed five runs _ four earned _ and six hits in four innings. He
was starting because Joey Hamilton was in San Diego with his wife
Angie, due to deliver their first child.
