<SLUG> BC-Sports-Baseball-US Awards,0221 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Belle, Cone, Guerrero, Park win baseball awards
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEW YORK (AP) _ Albert Belle and David Cone were honored Monday
by the AL as the top player and pitcher in the league in July.
Montreal's Vladimir Guerrero and Los Angeles' Chan Ho Park received
the NL honors.
	   Belle, of the Chicago White Sox, led the AL with 16 home runs
and a .941 slugging percentage in July. He also finished second
with 32 RBIs and a .406 batting average.
	   Fellow American Cone, of the New York Yankees, went 4-1 with a
0.69 for the month. In five starts, Cone pitched 39 innings, gave
up 31 hits, walked nine and struck out 36.
	   Guerrero, of the Dominican Republic, batted .385 with 11 home
runs and 27 RBIs. He scored 24 runs, had nine doubles and posted a
.771 slugging percentage and .438 on-base percentage.
	   Park, of South Korea, went 4-0 in July with a 1.05 ERA. In 42
2-3 innings, he struck out 34 and allowed 25 hits.
	   Boston's Nomar Garciaparra, of the United States, won the AL
Player of the Week award Monday. Garciaparra, who also received
votes for Player of the Month, hit .462 with three homers, eight
runs and 12 RBIs.
	   Houston right-hander Jose Lima, of the Dominican Republic, won
the NL Player of the Week, going 2-0 with a 1.00 ERA and 16
strikeouts in 18 innings.
</TEXT>
