BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROADCAST REQUESTED-
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY
NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
519 PM AST MON AUG 3 1998

...THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE IN SAN JUAN PR HAS ISSUED AN URBAN
AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY EFFECTIVE UNTIL 630 PM FOR THE
FOLLOWING MUNICIPALITIES IN NORTH CENTRAL PUERTO RICO...

...BARCELONETA...FLORIDA...ARECIBO...AND HATILLO...

AT 510 PM...THE WEATHER RADAR INDICATED STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WITH
INTENSE RAINFALL OVER THE NORTH CENTRAL SECTIONS OF PUERTO
RICO. RADAR ESTIMATES INDICATED MORE THAN TWO INCHES OF RAIN OVER THE
SOUTHERN SECTIONS OF ARECIBO. THESE THUNDERSTORMS WILL MOVE SLOWLY TO
THE NORTHWEST PRODUCING ADDITIONAL RAINFALL AND CONSEQUENTLY
URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOODING. MUD SLIDES ARE ALSO POSSIBLE IN
STEEP TERRAIN.

MOTORISTS AND PEDESTRIANS IN OR PASSING THROUGH THE AFFECTED AREA
THIS EVENING SHOULD AVOID CROSSING FLOODED ROADS...AND ALLOW
EXTRA TIME TO REACH THEIR DESTINATIONS.  REMEMBER...CARS CAN EASILY
STALL IN THE WATER AND BE CARRIED AWAY IN ANY CURRENT.  PEDESTRIANS
ARE ALSO ADVISED TO STAY AWAY FROM RISING CREEKS.  KEEP CHILDREN
AWAY FROM OPEN STORM DRAINS.
