<HEADLINE>

</HEADLINE>
BULLETIN-IMMEDIATE BROACAST REQUESTED
FLASH FLOOD STATEMENT
NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE SAN JUAN PR
641 PM AST MON AUG 3 1998

...THE URBAN AND SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY THAT WAS IN EFFECT FOR
THE MUNICIPALITIES OF BARCELONETA...FLORIDA...ARECIBO...AND HATILLO
HAS EXPIRED...

AT 635 PM...DOPPLER WEATHER RADAR INDICATED THAT THE STRONGEST
SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS THAT DEVELOPED ACROSS THE FORMER ADVISORY
AREA EARLIER THIS AFTERNOON HAVE WEAKENED AND HAVE MOVED TO THE
ADJACENT MUNICIPALITIES AND OVER THE COASTAL WATERS. NO REPORTS OF
OF FLOODING HAVE BEEN RECEIVED AND NO ADDITIONAL HEAVY RAINFALL IS
EXPECTED IN THIS AREA FOR THIS EVENING. THEREFORE...THE URBAN AND
SMALL STREAM FLOOD ADVISORY THAT WAS IN EFFECT HAS EXPIRED.

OTHER SHOWERS AND THUNDERSTORMS WERE OCCURRING OVER THE NORTHERN
SECTIONS OF SAN SEBASTIAN...QUEBRADILLAS AND ISABELA. THESE SHOWERS
AND THUNDERSTORMS MAY ALSO PRODUCE LOCALIZED FLOODING IN LOW AND
POOR DRAINAGE AREAS BEFORE DISSIPATED BY 700 PM.
