<HEADLINE>
MaliVai Washington advances in Toronto open
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS that Washington is American. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   TORONTO (AP) _ MaliVai Washington defeated No. 13 seed Jan
Siemerink of the Netherlands 7-6 (7-2), 6-3 on Monday to advance to
the second round of the dlrs 2.4 million du Maurier Open.
	   Washington, of teh United States, next faces Canada's Bobby
Kokavec, who downed Steve Campbell 6-1, 6-2 for his first match
victory on the ATP Tour.
	   ``MaliVai is obviously playing well,'' Kokavec said. ``I'm just
going to go after my shots and not change anything.''
	   Kokavec, honored Monday as Canada's most improved tennis player,
is ranked No. 347 in the world.
	   ``For me, ranking is just a number,'' Kokavec said. ``I feel
like anyone in the top 500 can beat anyone if they play good
because anybody can have a bad day.''
	   In other early matches, Australia's Scott Draper defeated
American Jim Courier 7-5, 5-7, 6-4 and Wayne Black of Zimbabwe beat
older brother Byron 6-4, 6-0.
	   Also, American Vince Spadea downed Australia's Andrew Illie 6-3,
6-0; Argentina's Guillermo Canada beat South Africa's Grant
Stafford 2-6, 7-6 (15-13), 6-2; South Africa's Neville Godwin
topped American Cecil Mamiit 6-4, 1-6, 6-4; and South Africa's
David Nainkin took Italy's Laurence Tieleman 6-1, 3-6, 7-5.
</TEXT>
