	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT:
	    &UR; NEW:
	   _IRAQ. Butler mission ending early after talks collapse.
	   _US-SELLING DANGER. U.S. inadvertently selling dangerous
military technology.
	   _SUDAN-PEACE TALKS. Peace talks to resume Tuesday.
 &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   UNITED NATIONS _ Talks between Iraq and the United Nations on
dismantling Iraq's weapons of mass destruction collapse and the
chief U.N. inspector is leaving Baghdad early. IRAQ. Lead has
moved, developments will be expedited. AP Photos BAG101-106.
	   KINSHASA, Congo _ His regime under threat from former allies,
President Laurent Kabila imposes a curfew on Congo's capital and
orders a manhunt for renegade Rwandan mercenaries. CONGO. Recap
expected by 0200 GMT. By Kamanga Mutond. AP Photo NY193.
	   With: CONGO-CHRONOLOGY.
	   PRISTINA, Yugoslavia _ International aid agencies struggle to
reach tens of thousands of refugees camped in the woods of Kosovo
province after fleeing Serb attacks. YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Recap
expected by 0200 GMT. By Anne Thompson. AP Photos PRI101-107.
	   ALSO MOVED: US-YUGOSLAVIA-KOSOVO. Clinton administration: NATO
has approved military plan for Kosovo.
	   JERUSALEM _ Israel and Palestinian negotiators end a crucial
late-night round of peace talks without commenting publicly.
ISRAEL-PALESTINIAN. Lead has moved; developments will be expedited.
By Danna Harman. AP Photo JRL101,105, GAZ101.
	   KABUL, Afghanistan _ The Taliban religious army pushes closes in
on a major opposition stronghold. AFGHANISTAN-FIGHTING. Lead has
moved. By Zaheeruddin Abdullah. AP Photo KAB101.
	   ALSO MOVED: UN-AFGHANISTAN. U.N. planning aid workers
evacuation.
	   ADDIS ABABA _ Representatives of the Sudanese government and
rebels fighting in southern Sudan open another round of talks
Tuesday aimed at ending the 15-year civil war. SUDAN-PEACE TALKS.
Expected by 0300 GMT. By Abebe Andualem.
	   ST. GEORGE'S, Grenada _ Fidel Castro wraps up a Caribbean tour
that helped shatter Cuba's isolation from its neighbors.
CARIBBEAN-CASTRO. Recap expected by 0300 GMT. By Michelle Faul. AP
Photos GRD101-2.
	   ALSO MOVED: US-CUBA. U.S. chides Caribbean countries for
inviting Castro.
	   WASHINGTON _President Bill Clinton's aides dampen speculation
that he will change his story about Monica Lewinsky. US-CLINTON
INVESTIGATION. Has moved. By John Solomon. AP Photo NYR101,
XWH101..
	   HANOVER, Germany _ Gerhard Schroeder, the frontrunner in the
race to be Germany's next leader, heads to Washington on Tuesday to
take on Helmut Kohl in the one area where the chancellor holds the
advantage: experience on the world stage. SCHROEDER-WASHINGTON
TRIP. Expected by 0200 GMT. By Colleen Barry. AP Photo FRA103.
	   CARACAS, Venezuela _ Former coup leader Hugo Chavez has been
attacked as a dictator-in-waiting, a populist demagogue, and a
criminal. He also may be Venezuela's next president. VENEZUELA-COUP
LEADER. Expected by 0200 GMT. By Bart Jones. AP Photos NY91.
	   ALGIERS, Algeria _ As a U.N. mission investigating a Muslim
insurgency wraps up its visit, officials report a massacre that
left at least 12 civilians dead. ALGERIA. Lead has moved. By Rachid
Khiari.
	   WASHINGTON _ Despite efforts to stop the inadvertent sale of
dangerous military equipment, the Pentagon still is unloading
surplus items around the world, a U.S. government report says.
US-SELLING DANGER. Has moved. By David Briscoe.
	   DENVER _ Researchers have successfully tested the first
DNA-based vaccine against rabies, a virus that has been well-known
for thousands of years and still annually kills 40,000 worldwide.
MED-US-RABIES. Expected by 0200 GMT. By Joseph B. Verrengia.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _BRITAIN-DIETING BY SMOKING. Study shows most teen-age girls who
take up smoking do so to lose weight.
	   _US-KIDS AND CHOLESTEROL. Daily exercise can start children on a
healthy path.
	   WASHINGTON _ After four years of ill will, the United States and
Colombia begin patching up relations, as Andres Pastrana visits the
White House ahead of his inauguration as Colombia's president.
US-COLOMBIA. Lead has moved. By Terence Hunt.
	   ALSO MOVED: COLOMBIA-PEACE. Rebels suspend peace talks with
civilian leaders.
	   BUENA VISTA, Virginia _ The mystery of two babies switched at
birth takes a sad, confusing twist with the discovery that the
couple raising one of the girls died in a car crash, never knowing
of the mix-up. US-SWITCHED BABIES. Recap expected by 0300 GMT. By
David Reed. AP Photo NY115.
	   LOOKING AHEAD: Croatia celebrates the third anniversary of its
capture of rebel Serb stronghold of Knin on Wednesday.
 &UR; FEATURES:
	   PUCHONG, Malaysia _ As nearly 2 million people in Kuala Lumpur
and its suburbs head into their sixth month of severe water
rationing, residents are at times seething or resigned.
FEA-MALAYSIA-WATER SHORTAGE. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Beth
Duff-Brown. AP Photo KL101.
 &UR; FEATURES: Business and Finance
	   NEW DELHI, India _ When the Indian government's
telecommunications monopoly ended, big names rushed in. Four years
later, companies like AT and T, Bell Canada and British Telecom,
are admitting their dreams were inflated. FEA-HELLO INDIA. Expected
by 0300 GMT. By Ashok Sharma. AP Photo NY339
	   PORT LOUIS, Mauritius _ Riding the crest of economic prosperity
fueled by the production and export of textiles and sportswear,
this island is again turning toward Africa _ for land, labor, and
investment opportunities. FEA-MAURITIUS-BACK TO AFRICA. Expected by
0300 GMT. By Susan Linnee. AP Photos NAI101-104.
	   WASHINGTON _ Talk about a morality tale turned upside down:
Free-spending Americans are the economic envy of the world, while
the Japanese, those industrious savers, are swamped by economic
troubles. FEA-US-SAVINGS MYSTERY. Expected by 0300 GMT. By Martin
Crutsinger.
	   NEW YORK _ Personal bankruptcy filings in the United States,
which have grown to record levels in recent years, will level off
this year and decline in 1999. FEA-US-BANKRUPTCY DECLINES. Expected
by 0300 GMT. By Patricia Lamiell.
