r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-Tennis-Toshiba     08-03 0323
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Tennis-Toshiba Classic,0322 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
France's Testud takes first day of competition
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   CARLSBAD, California (AP) _ Amateur American Alexandra Stevenson
lost concentration and with it a potential upset Monday in the
Toshiba Tennis Classic.
	   France's Sandrine Testud, ranked 13th in the world, was down a
set and trailed 2-1 in the second set before winning the final 11
games for a 4-6, 6-2, 6-0 victory on the opening day of the dlrs
450,000 event at the La Costa Resort and Spa.
	   Testud's comeback highlighted play on the first day of action in
the tournament featuring seven of the top 10 players on the WTA
tour.
	   None of the seeded players, including No. 1 seed Martina Hingis,
played on Monday.
	   Iva Majoli of Croatia, ranked 20th on the WTA tour but unseeded
here, was extended in a 7-6, (7-1), 6-3 victory over Alexandra
Fusai of France.
	   Former teen sensation Jennifer Capriati won her third qualifying
match _ a 7-6, (7-5), 2-6, 6-1 victory against France's Nathalie
Dechy _ to move into the main draw.
	   Stevenson, who will be a high school senior in the fall, was
playing in only her eighth WTA event. But the 17-year-old American
had never had the type of success she enjoyed Monday in taking a
lead into the second set against Testud.
	   Stevenson envisioned an upset that would improve her current
world ranking of No. 151.
	   ``I kept telling myself to stay focused,'' said Stevenson, who
has a 1-9 record on the WTA tour. ``I didn't think I played badly
but I got unfocused and made some errors.''
	   For Capriati, 22, the victory was another in her attempted
comeback from problems encountered as a teen tennis phenom.
	   Capriati has been an infrequent player since taking two years
off from the tour in 1994.
	   ``It's a humbling experience,'' Capriati said about having to
qualify for a tournament that she won in 1991 and 1992. ``But it
makes me more determined also.''
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-Sports-Tennis-Toshiba Classic; CT:s; 
(REG:EURO;)
(REG:BRIT;)
(REG:SCAN;)
(REG:MEST;)
(REG:AFRI;)
(REG:INDI;)
(REG:ENGL;)
(REG:ASIA;)
(LANG:ENGLISH;))
