<SLUG> BC-Sports-Olympics-Coin Program </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Sydney signs with USOC for coin marketing
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PERTH, Australia (AP) _ Coins commemorating the Sydney 2000
Games will be the most widely marketed in Olympic history following
the signing of a marketing agreement with the United States Olympic
Committee.
	   The Sydney Organizing Committee for the Olympic Games (SOCOG)
announced Tuesday that 21 months of negotiations had resulted in
the access marketing agreement through a wide range of distributors
in the United States.
	   ``A comprehensive marketing strategy has been developed to
ensure the broadest possible distribution of the coins throughout
the U.S.,'' committee executive Don Mackay-Coghill said in a
statement.
	   Access agreements to market Sydney 2000 coins pressed at the
Royal Australian Mint and the Perth Mint had already been signed
with 44 countries, and a further 16 were expected to join the
program, Mackay-Coghill said.
	   Eight gold coins, 16 silver and 28 aluminum bronze coins are
being released progressively between October of last year and May
2000. (djp) 	   
</TEXT>
